<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf6d5e4d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12376"><num value="12376">§ 12376.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbf6d5e4e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12376/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the term “Conference” means the 1993 White House Conference on Children, Youth, and Families; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbf6d5e4f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12376/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the terms “child”, “youth”, and “young individual” means <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn004048">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn004048"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “mean”.</note> an individual who is less than 21 years of age.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbf6d5e50-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/501/tIX/s987">Pub. L. 101–501, title IX, § 987</ref>, <date date="1990-11-03">Nov. 3, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1283">104 Stat. 1283</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbf6d5e51-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
